The '''Baobab Merchant Fleet''' was a trading fleet organized many years before the rise of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. Possessing a reputation as one of the finest merchant fleets in the galaxy, the [[Baobab family]] used its clout to establish the [[Baobab Archives]], an extensive repository for all sorts of knowledge.

Of note is the fact that the [[Bocce/Legends|Bocce]] language was developed for use in the Baobab Merchant Fleet, as the organization employed aliens of numerous races and needed a common method of communication.

After the rise of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], hard times fell on the Baobabs as they attempted to prevent their fleet from becoming Imperialized, much as the once-powerful [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] had been. The Baobab family seemed to dread the thought of their heir, [[Mungo Baobab]], taking over the business and leading them into ruin. Much to their surprise, he led not only the fleet but the Baobab name into the annals of history through the discovery of the lost [[Roonstone]]s.

Many historical figures, all part of the Baobab family, owned the fleet at some point, including Mungo and [[Ebenn Q3 Baobab/Legends|Ebenn Q3 Baobab]].

The Baobab Merchant Fleet logo was a stylized family crest crossed by two [[rainbow comet]]s.<ref name="CSWE">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref>

